.TH "xcsi2rxss_set_format" 9 "xcsi2rxss_set_format" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xcsi2rxss_set_format \- This is used to set the pad format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xcsi2rxss_set_format
.BI "(struct v4l2_subdev *sd "  ","
.BI "struct v4l2_subdev_pad_config *cfg "  ","
.BI "struct v4l2_subdev_format *fmt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sd" 12
Pointer to V4L2 Sub device structure
.IP "cfg" 12
Pointer to sub device pad information structure
.IP "fmt" 12
Pointer to pad level media bus format
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to set the pad format. Since the pad format is fixed
in hardware, it can't be modified on run time. So when a format set is
requested by application, all parameters except the format type is saved
for the pad and the original pad format is sent back to the application.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success
